15
00:00:12,104 --> 00:00:12,221
http://hiqve.co

16
00:00:12,222 --> 00:00:12,338
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,339 --> 00:00:12,456
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,457 --> 00:00:15,457
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,481 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>A planet of peace!</i>

20
00:00:20,775 --> 00:00:25,613
<i>The artisan colony of the planet Kiros
created a society without weapons.</i>

21
00:00:25,655 --> 00:00:29,367
<i>Instead of war,
they pursued art and beauty.</i>

22
00:00:29,450 --> 00:00:30,785
<i>But in the Clone Wars,</i>

23
00:00:30,826 --> 00:00:35,081
<i>even peace-loving worlds
are seemingly forced to change sides.</i>

24
00:00:36,666 --> 00:00:41,295
The simple truth is there is not a warrior
among us, Master Yoda.

25
00:00:41,379 --> 00:00:43,923
An armed conflict will destroy us.

26
00:00:43,965 --> 00:00:47,343
We will negotiate with Count Dooku
if we are able.

27
00:00:47,426 --> 00:00:51,389
<i>Trust Dooku, you cannot. Send help, I will.</i>

28
00:00:52,473 --> 00:00:54,559
I'm afraid it is too late.

29
00:00:56,269 --> 00:00:58,813
The Separatists have already arrived.

30
00:01:29,969 --> 00:01:34,181
Count Dooku, we have chosen
to remain neutral in this war.

31
00:01:34,223 --> 00:01:37,101
Why have you launched
this invasion against us?

32
00:01:37,184 --> 00:01:40,605
Think of our presence
as a peaceful occupation

33
00:01:40,688 --> 00:01:43,608
for your protection as well as ours.

34
00:01:43,691 --> 00:01:45,568
I have heard the tragic stories

35
00:01:45,651 --> 00:01:49,113
of worlds caught between your droids
and their clones.

36
00:01:49,196 --> 00:01:50,531
What of my people?

37
00:01:50,865 --> 00:01:56,746
While I am helpless to prevent the fighting,
I can offer your people sanctuary.

38
00:01:56,829 --> 00:02:00,374
A safe haven until the conflict has ended.

39
00:02:00,416 --> 00:02:04,253
Thank you, Count,
yours is a kind offer, but...

40
00:02:04,962 --> 00:02:06,714
I insist.

41
00:02:09,091 --> 00:02:12,136
Round up the citizens. All of them.

42
00:02:12,219 --> 00:02:13,721
Roger roger.

43
00:02:25,274 --> 00:02:27,485
-Unhand me.
-Watch it.

44
00:02:27,568 --> 00:02:30,363
-Hey! Let me go!
-Hey! Watch it!

45
00:02:30,404 --> 00:02:32,239
I said let me go!

46
00:02:41,457 --> 00:02:45,294
<i>All clear, sir.
There are no Separatist craft in the system.</i>

47
00:02:46,045 --> 00:02:49,173
It's been 10 rotations
since Master Yoda's transmission.

48
00:02:49,256 --> 00:02:51,050
I just hope we're not too late.

49
00:02:51,092 --> 00:02:54,095
-Rex. Take us down.
-Yes, sir.

50
00:03:43,978 --> 00:03:48,399
Anybody else think it's too quiet?
I haven't seen any colonists.

51
00:03:48,482 --> 00:03:51,318
-They're probably hiding.
-Let's hope they stay hidden.

52
00:03:51,402 --> 00:03:55,156
It makes our job easier if we don't have
to worry about them in battle.

53
00:03:55,239 --> 00:03:56,490
I don't like it.

54
00:03:56,574 --> 00:03:59,702
The clankers have never been shy
about using civvies as living shields.

55
00:04:00,161 --> 00:04:04,165
I'm sure they're here somewhere.
Let's make for the city center.

56
00:04:13,340 --> 00:04:15,050
Biker droids dead ahead!

57
00:04:15,134 --> 00:04:17,553
Squad, tighten up! Form on me!

58
00:04:59,845 --> 00:05:01,388
We're all clear, Master.

59
00:05:32,002 --> 00:05:34,588
Captain, have your men secure the area.

60
00:05:38,926 --> 00:05:40,928
How are we doing, Boil?

61
00:05:41,011 --> 00:05:43,055
We're still mopping up clankers here
and there, sir.

62
00:05:43,097 --> 00:05:45,599
We've established a perimeter
around the Governor's Tower.

63
00:05:45,641 --> 00:05:49,103
-No one gets out without a fight.
-Good work.

64
00:05:51,605 --> 00:05:54,650
Cody, any word
from the Separatist commander?

65
00:05:54,733 --> 00:05:58,487
He's barricaded inside.
His name is Darts D'Nar.

66
00:05:58,571 --> 00:06:00,948
He sent you a message, sir.

67
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:08,455
<i>Master Kenobi, come to the tower.
We will negotiate terms for surrender.</i>

68
00:06:08,497 --> 00:06:10,374
Well, that was easy.

69
00:06:12,793 --> 00:06:16,839
Zygerrian scum. I'll handle that slaver.

70
00:06:18,507 --> 00:06:20,759
Anakin, he asked for me.

71
00:06:20,801 --> 00:06:23,637
I need you to locate
the missing Togruta colonists.

72
00:06:24,889 --> 00:06:28,475
Fine. I'll have Admiral Yularen initiate
a planetary bio-scan.

73
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,694
Why is he so upset?

74
00:06:38,777 --> 00:06:42,531
Anakin has never talked about his past,
has he?

75
00:06:42,615 --> 00:06:45,117
Only to tell me he won't talk about it.

76
00:06:45,743 --> 00:06:50,831
As a child, Anakin and his mother were
sold into slavery by the Hutt clans.

77
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:53,709
Oh.

78
00:06:53,792 --> 00:06:56,670
And these Zygerrians, they're slavers?

79
00:06:57,463 --> 00:07:00,549
Anakin has struggled
to put his past behind him.

80
00:07:02,009 --> 00:07:05,012
Don't worry, I'll keep an eye on him.

81
00:07:05,304 --> 00:07:07,640
Yes, make sure you do.

82
00:07:21,654 --> 00:07:24,698
<i>The last shipment
has been received, D'Nar.</i>

83
00:07:24,782 --> 00:07:28,702
<i>I understand the Jedi have attacked.
Why are you still there?</i>

84
00:07:28,744 --> 00:07:32,206
I'm going to make the Jedi pay
for their arrogance.

85
00:07:32,247 --> 00:07:34,583
I have them right where I want them.

86
00:07:37,252 --> 00:07:38,587
Do tell.

87
00:07:42,549 --> 00:07:47,596
<i>Gentlemen, meet Obi-Wan Kenobi,
Jedi Knight.</i>

88
00:07:50,349 --> 00:07:55,437
<i>D'Nar, bring him to me on his knees.</i>

89
00:07:56,230 --> 00:07:57,898
With pleasure.

90
00:07:59,817 --> 00:08:02,444
We were going to discuss surrender?

91
00:08:02,528 --> 00:08:06,115
Yes. You will surrender.

92
00:08:06,198 --> 00:08:09,743
We obviously have a misunderstanding,
my friend.

93
00:08:14,248 --> 00:08:18,419
<i>- No, you are wrong, Jedi.</i>
<i>- Am I?</i>

94
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:21,088
<i>You are no doubt aware
your droid forces have been destroyed,</i>

95
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:22,506
and you are surrounded.

96
00:08:22,589 --> 00:08:25,342
Do the honorable thing
and give up now, D'Nar.

97
00:08:25,426 --> 00:08:28,053
I promise you will receive fair treatment.

98
00:08:28,095 --> 00:08:32,224
You've broken through my defenses.
You think you've won?

99
00:08:32,266 --> 00:08:34,101
Think again.

100
00:08:34,143 --> 00:08:37,062
I have planted bombs all over the city.

101
00:08:37,104 --> 00:08:38,981
<i>No one will survive.</i>

102
00:08:39,982 --> 00:08:42,317
<i>Now, surrender.</i>

103
00:08:42,401 --> 00:08:45,946
If you're not bluffing, then I must concede.

104
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:48,282
But you'll have to make considerations.

105
00:08:48,365 --> 00:08:50,409
First, you release the colonists.

106
00:08:50,951 --> 00:08:53,495
Here is my counter-offer.

107
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:10,095
There were no colonists in that structure,
but there could have been.

108
00:09:10,137 --> 00:09:14,600
Now, bow down and surrender to me,
you Jedi filth.

109
00:09:17,227 --> 00:09:19,480
I need a medic over here!

110
00:09:19,563 --> 00:09:21,648
Artoo, where are you?

111
00:09:22,941 --> 00:09:25,903
Watch yourself, buddy.
This is still a war zone.

112
00:09:25,986 --> 00:09:28,655
Cody! We don't have time
for the planetary scan.

113
00:09:28,697 --> 00:09:32,326
-Hook Artoo up, and he'll locate the bombs.
-Right away, sir!

114
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:35,954
-Ahsoka, let's go.
-Where are we going?

115
00:09:35,996 --> 00:09:39,166
To disarm the bombs
while Obi-Wan negotiates.

116
00:09:40,292 --> 00:09:42,586
I hope he can buy us some time.

117
00:09:45,839 --> 00:09:48,300
Very well, I surrender.

118
00:09:50,385 --> 00:09:52,471
Long before this war,

119
00:09:52,513 --> 00:09:56,683
you Jedi destroyed
the great Zygerrian Slave Empire.

120
00:09:56,725 --> 00:10:01,897
I would kill you now,
but Dooku would prefer you alive.

121
00:10:01,980 --> 00:10:04,525
I understand your frustration.

122
00:10:04,608 --> 00:10:07,361
It is unfortunate you
and I cannot resolve our differences

123
00:10:07,402 --> 00:10:09,738
as you do in the Zygerrian tradition.

124
00:10:15,702 --> 00:10:18,872
With no weapons, you would fight me?

125
00:10:18,956 --> 00:10:22,709
For good reason. Say, if I win,

126
00:10:22,793 --> 00:10:26,713
you reveal the location of the colonists
and the bombs.

127
00:10:29,174 --> 00:10:31,051
And if I win,

128
00:10:31,135 --> 00:10:35,472
I deliver you to Dooku in a cage
like one of these filthy creatures.

129
00:10:37,558 --> 00:10:38,684
Perhaps.

130
00:10:54,283 --> 00:10:57,411
Careful, you're disturbing my pets.

131
00:10:57,452 --> 00:10:59,580
They fetch a high price.

132
00:11:01,999 --> 00:11:03,000
General Skywalker!

133
00:11:03,083 --> 00:11:04,126
<i>Your droid is transmitting</i>

134
00:11:04,209 --> 00:11:06,420
<i>the bomb coordinates now.</i>

135
00:11:07,296 --> 00:11:10,591
Copy that, Cody.
We're approaching the first bomb now.

136
00:11:10,632 --> 00:11:12,092
Let's go!

137
00:11:15,596 --> 00:11:16,972
Do you hear that?

138
00:11:36,617 --> 00:11:40,204
There must be a wire we should cut
or something to stop the countdown.

139
00:11:40,287 --> 00:11:41,830
Stand back.

140
00:11:47,336 --> 00:11:48,378
Ah!

141
00:11:48,462 --> 00:11:52,049
-How did you know that would work?
-I trusted my instincts.

142
00:11:52,132 --> 00:11:53,800
You mean you guessed.

143
00:11:53,884 --> 00:11:58,430
Yeah, but it was an educated guess.
Now, come on. There's plenty more to go.

144
00:12:12,319 --> 00:12:16,531
For thousands of years,
Zygerria supplied slave labor to the galaxy.

145
00:12:18,951 --> 00:12:20,494
We prospered.

146
00:12:22,329 --> 00:12:23,997
Our customers prospered.

147
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:28,085
Then the Jedi came.

148
00:12:38,345 --> 00:12:42,933
<i>-Excuse me, sir. We have a problem.</i>
-What problem?

149
00:12:43,016 --> 00:12:46,812
<i>Our spotters are tracking
two enemy walkers moving through...</i>

150
00:12:57,739 --> 00:13:00,117
These are the last of them.

151
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:16,049
Defuse the bombs! I'll cover you!

152
00:13:20,262 --> 00:13:22,681
Master, I think the bombs are linked.

153
00:13:22,723 --> 00:13:26,018
You're supposed to disarm them,
not activate them!

154
00:13:26,059 --> 00:13:27,519
Droids on the roof!

155
00:13:28,854 --> 00:13:30,063
If they're connected,

156
00:13:30,105 --> 00:13:33,150
we'll have to defuse them at the same time.

157
00:13:37,404 --> 00:13:38,447
Snipers!

158
00:13:50,792 --> 00:13:52,294
Their shields are too strong!

159
00:14:01,678 --> 00:14:03,889
Come on, Anakin. Hurry up.

160
00:14:15,317 --> 00:14:18,487
I'm pinned down !
Master, we're running out of time!

161
00:14:20,197 --> 00:14:23,450
I know.
We have to do something and quick!

162
00:14:29,081 --> 00:14:32,751
Ahsoka, they're weak from the side.
I've got an angle on your droid.

163
00:14:35,962 --> 00:14:40,300
Okay. I've got a view of yours too.
Same time. Ready?

164
00:14:42,135 --> 00:14:43,303
Go!

165
00:14:56,650 --> 00:15:00,654
- That was a close one.
- Let's hope Obi-Wan shares our luck.

166
00:15:27,431 --> 00:15:31,101
Now I'll take revenge for my people, Jedi.

167
00:15:31,768 --> 00:15:34,521
Sir, you have an urgent transmission.

168
00:15:34,563 --> 00:15:37,649
<i>Sorry to interrupt, sir,
but you weren't responding.</i>

169
00:15:37,691 --> 00:15:39,526
What is it?

170
00:15:39,651 --> 00:15:43,697
<i>Uh... The Jedi have disarmed your bombs.</i>

171
00:15:44,698 --> 00:15:46,241
What?

172
00:15:48,076 --> 00:15:50,412
Give me the detonator!

173
00:16:00,172 --> 00:16:03,049
Certainly took him long enough this time.

174
00:16:08,847 --> 00:16:11,433
Well, shall we discuss your surrender?

175
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:14,561
Again?

176
00:16:15,479 --> 00:16:18,773
I still have one bomb left, Jedi.

177
00:16:19,357 --> 00:16:20,901
Sir, how could you?

178
00:16:22,486 --> 00:16:24,571
No! No!

179
00:16:29,201 --> 00:16:31,912
Get it off! Get it off! Get it off!

180
00:16:31,953 --> 00:16:34,581
Get it off! Get it off! Get it off!

181
00:16:34,664 --> 00:16:36,625
Get it off! Get it off!

182
00:16:41,755 --> 00:16:45,091
Anakin ! Anakin, come in.

183
00:16:45,133 --> 00:16:47,802
<i>D'Nar is making his escape from the tower.</i>

184
00:16:47,886 --> 00:16:49,304
On our way!

185
00:16:50,889 --> 00:16:55,894
-We'll never catch him in time.
-I am not letting that slaver scum get away.

186
00:17:58,290 --> 00:18:01,876
-So, what's your plan?
-I'm open to ideas.

187
00:18:19,936 --> 00:18:22,606
Hungry, my pet?

188
00:18:22,689 --> 00:18:24,691
I'll feed you!

189
00:18:34,743 --> 00:18:36,494
Hold on!

190
00:18:36,536 --> 00:18:39,164
"Hold on"? Do I have a choice?

191
00:18:58,767 --> 00:19:02,228
-Master!
-Ahsoka, you're only making it angry!

192
00:19:02,312 --> 00:19:05,065
I'll handle this. Go stabilize the ship.

193
00:19:27,379 --> 00:19:32,717
Young Jedi,
you'll learn your place.

194
00:19:32,759 --> 00:19:35,845
I'm not so young anymore.

195
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:06,793
Gotcha.

196
00:20:11,131 --> 00:20:13,258
Mission accomplished, Master.

197
00:20:14,175 --> 00:20:16,469
Where are the colonists?

198
00:20:16,553 --> 00:20:18,596
I will tell you nothing.

199
00:20:21,307 --> 00:20:22,767
Where are they?

200
00:20:25,478 --> 00:20:27,021
Master.

201
00:20:31,151 --> 00:20:34,821
My queen is going
to bring back the royal slave auction

202
00:20:34,863 --> 00:20:37,824
as in the days before the Jedi.

203
00:20:37,866 --> 00:20:40,827
Zygerria will be rich and powerful again.

204
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:44,497
The Jedi will not stop us this time.

205
00:20:45,123 --> 00:20:47,208
We'll see about that.

206
00:20:53,339 --> 00:20:56,092
<i>General Skywalker, I ran the bio-scan twice,</i>

207
00:20:56,176 --> 00:20:57,594
<i>but the results were negative.</i>

208
00:20:57,677 --> 00:21:00,263
<i>Are you saying
the colonists are not in the city?</i>

209
00:21:00,346 --> 00:21:02,849
<i>I'm saying they're not even on the planet.</i>

210
00:21:02,891 --> 00:21:06,686
<i>The entire population appears
to have simply vanished.</i>

211
00:21:07,395 --> 00:21:11,065
<i>Vanished? That's impossible.
Those are my people.</i>

212
00:21:13,234 --> 00:21:16,237
Troubling is the return of the Zygerrians.

213
00:21:16,321 --> 00:21:20,909
It is likely they mean to use Dooku
to rebuild their slaver empire.

214
00:21:21,701 --> 00:21:24,454
<i>We cannot allow that, Master.</i>

215
00:21:24,537 --> 00:21:29,000
Agree I do, but first
find the colonists you must.

216
00:21:29,042 --> 00:21:31,252
In great danger, they are.

217
00:21:31,336 --> 00:21:33,171
What is it, Master?

218
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:38,218
Sense I do a darker hand in this mystery.

219
00:21:38,259 --> 00:21:43,223
Slavery, a great tool it is
for the rise of the Sith.

220
00:21:43,247 --> 00:21:48,247
http://hiqve.com/

